"""The length of a month varies from 28 to 31 days. In this exercise you will create
a program that reads the name of a month from the user as a string. Then your
program should display the number of days in that month. Display “28 or 29 days”
for February so that leap years are addressed."""

#title() will be used to convert a string into a title form, for example january to January.
month = input("Introduce the name of the month: ").title()
if month == "January" or month == "March" or month == "May" or month == "July" or month =="August" 
or month == "October" or month == "December":
	print("The month has 31 days")
elif month == "February":
	print("This month has 28 or 29 days. ")
elif month == "April" or month == "June" or month =="September" or month == "November":
	print("This month has 30 days")
else:
	print("Error, the month entered is invalid. ")
